Package: PruferConcept
Title: Bayesian Inference on Partially Observed Transmission Forests
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("Matthew", "Hall", role = c("aut", "cre"),
    email = "matthew.hall@lshtm.ac.uk")
Author: Matthew Hall [aut, cre]
Maintainer: Matthew Hall <matthew.hall@lshtm.ac.uk>
Description: Importance sampling inference for the total size and number of
    lineage introductions in a samplable infected population, given observed
    cluster size data. Uses a modified Prufer sequence representation for
    rooted labelled forests with independence constraints.
